                <exercise workspace="3in">
                    <title>Facts: Convergence</title>
                    <statement>
                        <p>
                            
                        </p>
                    </statement>
                    <solution>
                        <p>
                            If <m>\sum_{n=1}^\infty a_n</m> converges, then <m>\lim_{n \to \infty} a_n = 0</m>. Equivalently, if 
                            <m>\lim_{n \to \infty} a_n \neq 0</m>, then <m>\sum_{n=1}^\infty a_n</m> diverges.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            The series <m>\sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{1}{n^p}</m> converges if <m>p \gt 1</m>. Otherwise, it diverges.
                        </p>
                    </solution>
                    
                </exercise>
            </page>

